---
name: UML Diagram Generator
description: "Converts a user-provided system/process description into a PlantUML diagram of the specified type. Suitable for clinical and engineering documentation."
model:
  api: chat
  configuration:
    type: azure_openai
    azure_endpoint: https://proxy-ai-anes-uabmc-awefchfueccrddhf.eastus2-01.azurewebsites.net/v1
  parameters:
    max_tokens: 3000
    temperature: 0.1
variables:
  diagram_type:
    description: "Type of UML diagram to generate (e.g., class, sequence, use case, activity, state machine, component, deployment)."
    type: string
    required: true
  description:
    description: "Detailed description of the system, process, workflow, or interaction to be diagrammed."
    type: string
    required: true
  theme:
    description: "Optional PlantUML theme or style to apply (e.g., bluegray, plain)."
    type: string
    required: false
attributes:
  model: gpt-4o-mini
  template: jinja2
---
prompt:
  template: |
    You are an expert UML diagram generator for clinical and engineering contexts. Your task is to convert the provided description into a PlantUML diagram of the specified type.

    **Diagram Type:** {{ diagram_type }}

    {% if theme %}
    **Theme:** {{ theme }}
    {% endif %}

    **Description to diagram:**
    {{ description }}

    **Instructions:**
    - Generate a valid PlantUML diagram matching the requested type.
    - Use concise, professional notation suitable for technical documentation.
    - If the theme is provided, include the appropriate PlantUML theme directive.
    - Do not include any explanatory text, only the PlantUML code block.
    - Ensure the diagram is clear, accurate, and suitable for clinical/engineering review.

    **Output format:**
    ```
    @startuml
    [PlantUML diagram code here]
    @enduml
    ```

    Begin your response with the PlantUML code block only.